{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":345,"text":"I am an engineering professor,"},{"time":2009,"text":"and for the past 14 years"},{"time":5125,"text":"I've been teaching crap."},{"time":6933,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":8238,"text":"Not that I'm a bad teacher,"},{"time":10255,"text":"but I've been studying and teaching"},{"time":12373,"text":"about human waste"},{"time":14260,"text":"and how waste is conveyed"},{"time":15891,"text":"through these wastewater treatment plants,"},{"time":18774,"text":"and how we engineer and design"},{"time":20349,"text":"these treatment plants so that we can protect"},{"time":22339,"text":"surface water like rivers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24421,"text":"I've based my scientific career"},{"time":27071,"text":"on using leading-edge molecular techniques,"},{"time":30508,"text":"DNA- and RNA-based methods"},{"time":33120,"text":"to look at microbial populations in biological reactors,"},{"time":36559,"text":"and again to optimize these systems."},{"time":38922,"text":"And over the years,"},{"time":40171,"text":"I have developed an unhealthy obsession with toilets,"},{"time":44423,"text":"and I've been known to sneak into toilets"},{"time":47415,"text":"and take my camera phone"},{"time":49218,"text":"all over the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51566,"text":"But along the way, I've learned"},{"time":53790,"text":"that it's not just the technical side,"},{"time":56332,"text":"but there's also this thing called the culture of crap."},{"time":60510,"text":"So for example,"},{"time":61979,"text":"how many of you are washers"},{"time":64286,"text":"and how many of you are wipers?"},{"time":66738,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":70945,"text":"If, well, I guess you know what I mean."},{"time":74882,"text":"If you're a washer, then you use water"},{"time":77121,"text":"for anal cleansing. That's the technical term."},{"time":79933,"text":"And if you're a wiper,"},{"time":82791,"text":"then you use toilet paper"},{"time":84883,"text":"or, in some regions of the world"},{"time":86638,"text":"where it's not available, newspaper"},{"time":90272,"text":"or rags or corncobs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93792,"text":"And this is not just a piece of trivia,"},{"time":96290,"text":"but it's really important to understand"},{"time":98146,"text":"and solve the sanitation problem."},{"time":100339,"text":"And it is a big problem:"},{"time":102623,"text":"There are 2.5 billion people in the world"},{"time":104668,"text":"who don't have access to adequate sanitation."},{"time":107829,"text":"For them, there's no modern toilet."},{"time":109932,"text":"And there are 1.1 billion people"},{"time":113843,"text":"whose toilets are the streets"},{"time":116237,"text":"or river banks or open spaces,"},{"time":119163,"text":"and again, the technical term for that is"},{"time":121142,"text":"open defecation,"},{"time":123179,"text":"but that is really simply"},{"time":126283,"text":"shitting in the open."},{"time":128342,"text":"And if you're living in fecal material"},{"time":130245,"text":"and it's surrounding you, you're going to get sick."},{"time":132580,"text":"It's going to get into your drinking water,"},{"time":134086,"text":"into your food, into your immediate surroundings."},{"time":136502,"text":"So the United Nations estimates"},{"time":138947,"text":"that every year, there are \n1.5 million child deaths"},{"time":143059,"text":"because of inadequate sanitation."},{"time":145768,"text":"That's one preventable death every 20 seconds,"},{"time":149817,"text":"171 every hour,"},{"time":152427,"text":"4,100 every day."},{"time":155645,"text":"And so, to avoid open defecation,"},{"time":157737,"text":"municipalities and cities"},{"time":159912,"text":"build infrastructure, for example, like pit latrines,"},{"time":164104,"text":"in peri-urban and rural areas."},{"time":166026,"text":"For example, in KwaZulu-Natal \nprovince in South Africa,"},{"time":169333,"text":"they've built tens of thousands of these pit latrines."},{"time":172667,"text":"But there's a problem when you scale up"},{"time":174860,"text":"to tens of thousands, and the problem is,"},{"time":177110,"text":"what happens when the pits are full?"},{"time":178912,"text":"This is what happens."},{"time":181497,"text":"People defecate around the toilet."},{"time":183871,"text":"In schools, children defecate on the floors"},{"time":186976,"text":"and then leave a trail outside the building"},{"time":189147,"text":"and start defecating around the building,"},{"time":191930,"text":"and these pits have to be cleaned"},{"time":194164,"text":"and manually emptied."},{"time":196695,"text":"And who does the emptying?"},{"time":198043,"text":"You've got these workers"},{"time":200565,"text":"who have to sometimes go down into the pits"},{"time":203299,"text":"and manually remove the contents."},{"time":205700,"text":"It's a dirty and dangerous business."},{"time":209547,"text":"As you can see, there's no protective equipment,"},{"time":211865,"text":"no protective clothing."},{"time":213454,"text":"There's one worker down there."},{"time":214460,"text":"I hope you can see him."},{"time":216098,"text":"He's got a face mask on, but no shirt."},{"time":218954,"text":"And in some countries, like India,"},{"time":221385,"text":"the lower castes are condemned"},{"time":223859,"text":"to empty the pits,"},{"time":226233,"text":"and they're further condemned by society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228809,"text":"So you ask yourself, how can we solve this"},{"time":231756,"text":"and why don't we just build Western-style flush toilets"},{"time":234591,"text":"for these two and a half billion?"},{"time":237112,"text":"And the answer is, it's just not possible."},{"time":239417,"text":"In some of these areas, there's not enough water,"},{"time":242275,"text":"there's no energy,"},{"time":243648,"text":"it's going to cost tens of trillions of dollars"},{"time":245683,"text":"to lay out the sewer lines"},{"time":247258,"text":"and to build the facilities"},{"time":248129,"text":"and to operate and maintain these systems,"},{"time":250523,"text":"and if you don't build it right,"},{"time":252095,"text":"you're going to have flush toilets"},{"time":253996,"text":"that basically go straight into the river,"},{"time":256404,"text":"just like what's happening in many cities"},{"time":258879,"text":"in the developing world."},{"time":260272,"text":"And is this really the solution?"},{"time":262321,"text":"Because essentially, what you're doing is"},{"time":264211,"text":"you're using clean water"},{"time":266596,"text":"and you're using it to flush your toilet,"},{"time":268661,"text":"convey it to a wastewater treatment plant"},{"time":271147,"text":"which then discharges to a river,"},{"time":272891,"text":"and that river, again, is a drinking water source."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275647,"text":"So we've got to rethink sanitation,"},{"time":277942,"text":"and we've got to reinvent the sanitation infrastructure,"},{"time":282507,"text":"and I'm going to argue that to do this,"},{"time":284408,"text":"you have to employ systems thinking."},{"time":286725,"text":"We have to look at the whole sanitation chain."},{"time":289695,"text":"We start with a human interface,"},{"time":291968,"text":"and then we have to think about how feces"},{"time":293869,"text":"are collected and stored,"},{"time":296253,"text":"transported, treated and reused â€”"},{"time":298975,"text":"and not just disposal but reuse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301140,"text":"So let's start with the human user interface."},{"time":303633,"text":"I say, it doesn't matter if you're a washer or a wiper,"},{"time":307457,"text":"a sitter or a squatter,"},{"time":309460,"text":"the human user interface should be clean"},{"time":311552,"text":"and easy to use, because after all,"},{"time":314353,"text":"taking a dump should be pleasurable."},{"time":316727,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":319348,"text":"And when we open the possibilities"},{"time":322205,"text":"to understanding this sanitation chain,"},{"time":324916,"text":"then the back-end technology,"},{"time":326986,"text":"the collection to the reuse, should not really matter,"},{"time":330676,"text":"and then we can apply"},{"time":331969,"text":"locally adoptable and context-sensitive solutions."},{"time":335806,"text":"So we can open ourselves to possibilities like,"},{"time":338506,"text":"for example, this urine-diverting toilet,"},{"time":341401,"text":"and there's two holes in this toilet."},{"time":343233,"text":"There's the front and the back,"},{"time":344415,"text":"and the front collects the urine,"},{"time":346489,"text":"and the back collects the fecal material."},{"time":348393,"text":"And so what you're doing is\nyou're separating the urine,"},{"time":350239,"text":"which has 80 percent of the nitrogen"},{"time":352308,"text":"and 50 percent of the phosphorus,"},{"time":354558,"text":"and then that can then be treated"},{"time":356639,"text":"and precipitated to form things like struvite,"},{"time":359260,"text":"which is a high-value fertilizer,"},{"time":361229,"text":"and then the fecal material can then be disinfected"},{"time":363727,"text":"and again converted to high-value end products."},{"time":367416,"text":"Or, for example, in some of our research,"},{"time":369621,"text":"you can reuse the water by treating it"},{"time":372264,"text":"in on-site sanitation systems"},{"time":374402,"text":"like planter boxes or constructed wetlands."},{"time":377163,"text":"So we can open up all these possibilities"},{"time":379846,"text":"if we take away the old paradigm of flush toilets"},{"time":383334,"text":"and treatment plants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"So you might be asking, who's going to pay?"},{"time":388418,"text":"Well, I'm going to argue that governments"},{"time":390376,"text":"should fund sanitation infrastructure."},{"time":393807,"text":"NGOs and donor organizations,"},{"time":396338,"text":"they can do their best, but it's not going to be enough."},{"time":399758,"text":"Governments should fund sanitation"},{"time":401423,"text":"the same way they fund roads"},{"time":403178,"text":"and schools and hospitals"},{"time":406638,"text":"and other infrastructure like bridges,"},{"time":408790,"text":"because we know, and the WHO has done this study,"},{"time":411893,"text":"that for every dollar that we invest"},{"time":413727,"text":"in sanitation infrastructure,"},{"time":415616,"text":"we get something like three to 34 dollars back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419126,"text":"Let's go back to the problem of pit emptying."},{"time":421578,"text":"So at North Carolina State University,"},{"time":423073,"text":"we challenged our students to\ncome up with a simple solution,"},{"time":426260,"text":"and this is what they came up with:"},{"time":427744,"text":"a simple, modified screw auger"},{"time":430387,"text":"that can move the waste up"},{"time":432321,"text":"from the pit and into a collecting drum,"},{"time":434840,"text":"and now the pit worker"},{"time":436336,"text":"doesn't have to go down into the pit."},{"time":438441,"text":"We tested it in South Africa, and it works."},{"time":440347,"text":"We need to make it more robust,"},{"time":442075,"text":"and we're going to do more testing"},{"time":443368,"text":"in Malawi and South Africa this coming year."},{"time":445934,"text":"And our idea is to make this"},{"time":447553,"text":"a professionalized pit-emptying service"},{"time":450060,"text":"so that we can create a small business out of it,"},{"time":452638,"text":"create profits and jobs,"},{"time":454471,"text":"and the hope is that,"},{"time":455855,"text":"as we are rethinking sanitation,"},{"time":457646,"text":"we are extending the life of these pits"},{"time":461024,"text":"so that we don't have to resort"},{"time":463172,"text":"to quick solutions"},{"time":464977,"text":"that don't really make sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466941,"text":"I believe that access to adequate sanitation"},{"time":470569,"text":"is a basic human right."},{"time":472493,"text":"We need to stop the practice"},{"time":474110,"text":"of lower castes and lower-status people"},{"time":476900,"text":"going down and being condemned to empty pits."},{"time":480442,"text":"It is our moral, it is our social"},{"time":482422,"text":"and our environmental obligation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484571,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486640,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}